1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,033


2
00:00:53,710 --> 00:00:55,240
Yes, hello?

3
00:00:56,080 --> 00:00:57,880
My name is Nase Izumi.

4
00:00:57,880 --> 00:01:00,080
Nase? The Nase?

5
00:01:00,080 --> 00:01:01,320
Yes.

6
00:01:01,320 --> 00:01:04,410
I'm calling with some news for you.

7
00:02:12,240 --> 00:02:13,780
Kuriyama Mirai-san?

8
00:02:15,200 --> 00:02:16,560
Pleased to meet you.

9
00:02:16,560 --> 00:02:17,900
I'm Nase Izumi.

10
00:02:18,650 --> 00:02:19,780
This is Kuriyama Mirai.

11
00:02:20,210 --> 00:02:23,030
A spirit hunter and legitimate successor of the cursed bloodline.

12
00:02:23,030 --> 00:02:28,630
Do you mean the clan that is
shunned by most spirit hunters?

13
00:02:28,630 --> 00:02:29,540
Yes.

14
00:02:30,110 --> 00:02:31,330
Kuriyama-san.

15
00:02:41,390 --> 00:02:44,530
She can use her own blood as a weapon.

16
00:02:44,530 --> 00:02:50,650
Not only can it be hardened, it can also be used as a lethal poison that erodes bodily tissue.

17
00:02:50,650 --> 00:02:53,070
Will that be enough?

18
00:02:53,070 --> 00:02:54,900
It's hard to say.

19
00:02:54,900 --> 00:02:57,150
But I believe she stands a very good chance.

20
00:02:57,150 --> 00:03:00,810
Isn't the target said to be immortal?

21
00:03:00,810 --> 00:03:02,280
Yes.

22
00:03:02,930 --> 00:03:03,880
Immortal?

23
00:03:03,880 --> 00:03:08,510
In truth, he's just terrifyingly quick to recover,

24
00:03:08,510 --> 00:03:12,710
but he's known to the spirit hunters
around here as the "immortal half-shade."

25
00:03:13,530 --> 00:03:15,590
The immortal half-shade?

26
00:03:16,210 --> 00:03:17,210
Let me show you.

27
00:03:19,580 --> 00:03:25,520
\hUnlike shadelings, he's half human and half shade—a preposterous and dangerous being.

28
00:03:25,520 --> 00:03:30,310
My research showed me that his shade half resembles the shade beyond the horizon.

29
00:03:30,310 --> 00:03:34,720
My younger brother attempted to kill this fellow
but had the tables turned on him.

30
00:03:34,720 --> 00:03:36,930
He nearly died from his injuries.

31
00:03:38,780 --> 00:03:40,400
You're the only one I can count on.

32
00:03:40,900 --> 00:03:41,990
Please.

33
00:03:43,190 --> 00:03:48,660
This is the shade from beyond the horizon?

34
00:03:49,570 --> 00:03:53,860
Sorry for dragging you along to
that stifling meeting back there.

35
00:03:53,860 --> 00:03:57,490
It may be because of this area's long history, but we have certain customs.

36
00:03:57,490 --> 00:03:58,820
Bonsai?

37
00:03:58,820 --> 00:03:59,960
Yes.

38
00:03:59,960 --> 00:04:01,240
Um, that aside...

39
00:04:01,240 --> 00:04:02,150
What?

40
00:04:02,150 --> 00:04:05,090
Where's this shade from beyond the horizon?

41
00:04:05,090 --> 00:04:06,540
Rest assured.

42
00:04:06,540 --> 00:04:08,530
He's under constant supervision.

43
00:04:08,530 --> 00:04:11,640
I'll have to kill him sooner or later, right?

44
00:04:11,640 --> 00:04:13,320
Then I'd prefer it to be sooner.

45
00:04:13,320 --> 00:04:13,850
Can you?

46
00:04:15,080 --> 00:04:17,520
How should I know?!

47
00:04:17,520 --> 00:04:18,820
You had no idea either—

48
00:04:17,980 --> 00:04:18,820
That's not it.

49
00:04:19,600 --> 00:04:23,100
I'm asking you if you're mentally prepared for this.

50
00:04:34,420 --> 00:04:37,670
The half-shade's name is Kanbara Akihito.

51
00:04:47,260 --> 00:04:48,600
Suicide.

52
00:04:49,730 --> 00:04:56,200
Defined in the dictionary as "the act of taking one's own life,"

53
00:04:56,200 --> 00:05:01,080
it's something I will probably never even think about doing.

54
00:05:02,910 --> 00:05:06,030
Not because I think it's unethical,

55
00:05:06,030 --> 00:05:09,580
but for a more fundamental reason.

56
00:05:09,580 --> 00:05:12,240
However, let's save that for later.

57
00:05:12,890 --> 00:05:15,500
Right now, she's about to die.

58
00:05:16,610 --> 00:05:19,240
At least, it seemed like that to me.

59
00:05:19,850 --> 00:05:24,540
At this point the story can proceed in one of two ways.

60
00:05:24,540 --> 00:05:30,200
Either the protagonist plays an active role in the events that unfold,

61
00:05:30,200 --> 00:05:36,140
or he takes a passive role as the story moves on without him.

62
00:05:36,660 --> 00:05:39,690
By all accounts, I'd fall into the latter category,

63
00:05:39,690 --> 00:05:42,980
but for some reason, I chose the former option at this time.

64
00:05:44,400 --> 00:05:45,820
H-Hey!

65
00:05:50,520 --> 00:05:53,580
I won't repeat everything I said, but...

66
00:05:53,580 --> 00:05:58,170
"...at any rate, someone who looks as good in glasses as you

67
00:05:58,170 --> 00:05:59,630
simply must not die!"

68
00:06:00,030 --> 00:06:03,000
That was my heartfelt plea to her.

69
00:06:04,250 --> 00:06:08,220
I finished by screaming out everything I felt at that moment.

70
00:06:08,220 --> 00:06:10,510
"Basically, I love glasses!"

71
00:06:12,240 --> 00:06:13,390
How unpleasant.

72
00:06:23,810 --> 00:06:25,030
You—

73
00:06:30,710 --> 00:06:33,150
You picked a fight with the wrong person.

74
00:06:36,030 --> 00:06:37,720
Hey, uh...

75
00:06:37,720 --> 00:06:41,750
Think you could at least do something about this sword?

76
00:06:41,750 --> 00:06:43,710
Please?

77
00:06:48,190 --> 00:06:51,620
And that's how I met Kuriyama Mirai.

78
00:06:52,320 --> 00:06:56,870
If our story had ended after a meeting like that,

79
00:06:56,870 --> 00:07:01,000
I don't think any story in this world would be worth telling.

80
00:07:02,940 --> 00:07:08,360
Beyond the Boundary

81
00:07:25,210 --> 00:07:26,040
Did she give up?

82
00:07:27,380 --> 00:07:28,880
Where did you even come from?!

83
00:07:35,100 --> 00:07:35,950
Take this!

84
00:07:40,650 --> 00:07:42,460
Hey, we can't go around destroying buckets!

85
00:07:48,660 --> 00:07:49,320
Jeez!

86
00:08:15,010 --> 00:08:17,470
I think it's about time we put an end to this.

87
00:08:18,610 --> 00:08:19,850
What is this, a horror movie?

88
00:08:23,380 --> 00:08:24,960
E-Everything's dark!

89
00:08:24,960 --> 00:08:25,940
What'd you do to me?!

90
00:08:26,400 --> 00:08:28,140
It's just a bucket.

91
00:08:36,210 --> 00:08:38,280
Are you hungry?

92
00:08:38,690 --> 00:08:39,950
What's the big deal?

93
00:08:39,950 --> 00:08:41,160
It's not like you lose anything!

94
00:08:41,160 --> 00:08:42,520
Of course I do!

95
00:08:42,520 --> 00:08:44,290
You keep chipping away at what's left of my heart!

96
00:08:44,290 --> 00:08:46,690
I told you I still feel pain, didn't I?!

97
00:08:46,690 --> 00:08:48,850
Do you have any idea how much it hurts?

98
00:08:48,850 --> 00:08:52,120
Doing whatever you please to us immortals
is just discrimination!

99
00:08:52,120 --> 00:08:53,470
People are going to hear you, you know.

100
00:08:53,470 --> 00:08:54,960
It's fine.

101
00:08:54,960 --> 00:08:56,640
I already made sure no one else was around.

102
00:08:56,640 --> 00:08:58,680
Thanks for waiting.

103
00:08:58,680 --> 00:09:03,520
Here are your extra burrito, mole poblano, and chili con carne combos.

104
00:09:03,520 --> 00:09:04,980
Enjoy yourselves.

105
00:09:04,980 --> 00:09:06,880
You ordered even more food?!

106
00:09:06,880 --> 00:09:07,730
You're being unpleasant.

107
00:09:07,730 --> 00:09:10,280
I'm the one who's finding this unpleasant!

108
00:09:10,280 --> 00:09:11,960
Not only do you practice on me,

109
00:09:11,960 --> 00:09:14,010
you even have the nerve to mooch off me for dinner!

110
00:09:14,010 --> 00:09:15,380
Mooch?

111
00:09:15,380 --> 00:09:18,160
I thought we had a deal.

112
00:09:18,160 --> 00:09:21,160
I'd refrain from challenging you to any more fights tonight, and in exchange,

113
00:09:21,160 --> 00:09:22,920
you'd treat me to dinner.

114
00:09:22,920 --> 00:09:26,400
So that means you're going to attack me again tomorrow, I take it?

115
00:09:26,400 --> 00:09:28,110
Why wouldn't I?

116
00:09:37,300 --> 00:09:38,600
Kuriyama-san!

117
00:09:38,600 --> 00:09:39,750
Are you alright?

118
00:09:40,380 --> 00:09:41,670
I'm fine.

119
00:09:41,670 --> 00:09:42,760
Just a little anemic.

120
00:09:42,760 --> 00:09:45,520
I was using my blood, after all.

121
00:09:47,910 --> 00:09:50,940
Let's take this to Ayaka-san tomorrow.

122
00:09:50,940 --> 00:09:53,440
I'll come pick you up in the morning.

123
00:09:53,940 --> 00:09:56,210
You shouldn't get too close to me.

124
00:09:56,210 --> 00:10:00,140
I've unleashed powers I normally keep in check.

125
00:10:00,140 --> 00:10:03,910
Immortal or not, you don't want to touch my blood right now.

126
00:10:03,910 --> 00:10:06,870
We still have to do something about that bleeding.

127
00:10:09,550 --> 00:10:10,950
Give me your hand.

128
00:10:13,250 --> 00:10:14,500
I'll do it myself.

129
00:10:14,500 --> 00:10:15,920
Come on.

130
00:10:20,090 --> 00:10:22,850
Kuriyama-san, you haven't joined a club yet, have you?

131
00:10:22,850 --> 00:10:25,100
I don't have time for that.

132
00:10:25,100 --> 00:10:27,100
I can't interest you in the Literature Club?

133
00:10:27,100 --> 00:10:28,100
Why do you ask?

134
00:10:28,100 --> 00:10:30,350
Because I'd love for a beauty with glasses to join.

135
00:10:30,350 --> 00:10:31,860
How unpleasant.

136
00:10:32,430 --> 00:10:34,710
Well, it's the club I'm in,

137
00:10:34,710 --> 00:10:36,360
and we only have two real members right now.

138
00:10:37,100 --> 00:10:38,820
Oh, and the other one's a spirit hunter too,

139
00:10:38,820 --> 00:10:41,840
so I'm sure it'd work in your favor professionally as well.

140
00:10:43,620 --> 00:10:45,310
I'll have to pass.

141
00:10:45,310 --> 00:10:47,000
Huh? Why?

142
00:10:47,000 --> 00:10:50,250
I don't want to associate with other people...

143
00:10:55,250 --> 00:11:00,140
I guess his immortality really can't
be dealt with using normal methods.

144
00:11:00,140 --> 00:11:00,760
Yes.

145
00:11:01,400 --> 00:11:03,870
You should observe him for a while.

146
00:11:03,870 --> 00:11:07,690
Attacking him haphazardly won't get you anywhere.

147
00:11:07,690 --> 00:11:08,230
But...

148
00:11:08,860 --> 00:11:13,810
In time, his shade half is sure to surface again,
as it did against Hiro'omi.

149
00:11:14,280 --> 00:11:16,390
Use that opportunity.

150
00:11:16,390 --> 00:11:17,610
Okay.

151
00:11:18,030 --> 00:11:19,350
Also...

152
00:11:21,160 --> 00:11:22,570
Let me offer you a warning.

153
00:11:23,240 --> 00:11:26,680
You'd be better off keeping
your distance from Akihito-kun.

154
00:11:28,530 --> 00:11:29,560
Oh, right.

155
00:11:29,560 --> 00:11:30,410
Kuriyama-san.

156
00:11:30,410 --> 00:11:31,420
Y-Yes?

157
00:11:31,420 --> 00:11:34,350
Remember what we talked about yesterday? How about it?

158
00:11:34,350 --> 00:11:37,300
I want to invite her to come visit the Literature Club. Is that okay?

159
00:11:37,780 --> 00:11:39,590
She says she hasn't joined any clubs,

160
00:11:39,590 --> 00:11:42,540
and there aren't many other spirit hunters at our school.

161
00:11:42,540 --> 00:11:43,800
Besides, she only just got here—

162
00:11:43,800 --> 00:11:46,930
I thought I refused already.

163
00:11:50,480 --> 00:11:51,730
I'm scared.

164
00:11:52,510 --> 00:11:54,370
I'm terrified of taking lives.

165
00:11:55,850 --> 00:11:57,940
Then why don't you quit being a spirit hunter?

166
00:11:59,170 --> 00:12:01,430
If I could...

167
00:12:01,430 --> 00:12:03,860
If I could, I would've done so a long time ago!

168
00:12:04,560 --> 00:12:06,560
I tried to quit!

169
00:12:06,560 --> 00:12:08,070
I tried to quit being a spirit hunter,

170
00:12:08,070 --> 00:12:10,200
quit killing dreamshades,

171
00:12:10,200 --> 00:12:12,040
and live a normal life!

172
00:12:13,130 --> 00:12:16,290
But this cursed blood flowing through my veins is anything but normal.

173
00:12:17,180 --> 00:12:19,180
This power of mine...

174
00:12:20,450 --> 00:12:22,420
The same goes for me.

175
00:12:29,600 --> 00:12:33,350
Why would you say that?

176
00:12:34,160 --> 00:12:35,320
Why...

177
00:12:37,370 --> 00:12:40,110
You're an investigator from the Spirit Hunter Association's Observation Bureau?

178
00:12:40,110 --> 00:12:41,170
That's right.

179
00:12:41,170 --> 00:12:45,270
I'm Fujima Miroku. Nice to meet you, Nase Izumi-san.

180
00:12:45,270 --> 00:12:47,370
So, what is your business here?

181
00:12:47,370 --> 00:12:49,710
The Hollow Shadow.

182
00:12:49,710 --> 00:12:53,000
Dreamshades this powerful don't show up too often,

183
00:12:53,000 --> 00:12:55,000
so I'm here to observe it.

184
00:12:56,240 --> 00:12:58,250
Dreams mark the way to the underworld.

185
00:12:59,020 --> 00:13:04,010
And we call the darkness that lies within them "dreamshades," masses of human resentment

186
00:13:04,640 --> 00:13:09,060
brought to life by the twisted human heart and all of its hatred, envy, and aggression.

187
00:13:09,060 --> 00:13:12,370
Dreamshades will continue to exist as long as humans do.

188
00:13:12,370 --> 00:13:15,270
So long as we can see them, we will continue to kill them.

189
00:13:15,270 --> 00:13:18,740
Doesn't that make you feel like spirit hunting thrives on the misery of others?

190
00:13:22,630 --> 00:13:24,780
I see you have some interesting views on the subject.

191
00:13:26,300 --> 00:13:27,490
How so?

192
00:13:27,490 --> 00:13:33,630
Having descended from a long line of spirit hunters
that have been fighting shades since antiquity,

193
00:13:33,630 --> 00:13:35,840
I see shades the same way a farmer sees rice,

194
00:13:35,840 --> 00:13:38,240
or a fisherman sees fish.

195
00:13:38,240 --> 00:13:40,650
It doesn't matter what they are.

196
00:13:40,650 --> 00:13:42,120
I see.

197
00:13:43,170 --> 00:13:45,570
May I ask you something?

198
00:13:45,570 --> 00:13:46,550
Go ahead.

199
00:13:47,460 --> 00:13:50,050
What are dreamshades to you?

200
00:13:51,640 --> 00:13:53,060
That goes without saying, doesn't it?

201
00:13:54,120 --> 00:13:56,060
Monsters, nothing more.

202
00:13:57,310 --> 00:13:58,060
Do I...

203
00:13:59,420 --> 00:14:01,230
look like a normal person...

204
00:14:02,560 --> 00:14:03,970
to you?

205
00:14:10,300 --> 00:14:11,070
In my eyes,

206
00:14:11,070 --> 00:14:14,580
you're nothing but a bespectacled beauty.

207
00:14:23,150 --> 00:14:25,000
What... the...

208
00:14:26,320 --> 00:14:28,430
The Hollow Shadow?

209
00:14:37,980 --> 00:14:39,940
Kuriyama-san...

210
00:14:40,300 --> 00:14:41,600
Hurry up...

211
00:14:42,950 --> 00:14:43,820
And stab me!

212
00:14:45,320 --> 00:14:47,700
It's in a weakened state right now, isn't it?

213
00:14:47,700 --> 00:14:51,580
Chase it out of my body and you'll be able to finish it off!

214
00:14:51,580 --> 00:14:53,030
But you'll...

215
00:14:53,030 --> 00:14:55,130
I won't die.

216
00:14:55,130 --> 00:14:56,620
I'm immortal, after all.

217
00:15:02,220 --> 00:15:03,210
I won't last much longer.

218
00:15:03,650 --> 00:15:04,550
Hurry up!

219
00:15:04,550 --> 00:15:05,590
B-But...

220
00:15:05,920 --> 00:15:08,970
Isn't this what you came here to do?

221
00:15:08,970 --> 00:15:12,360
Didn't you come here telling yourself you had to do this?

222
00:15:12,360 --> 00:15:14,470
Y-Yes, but...

223
00:15:14,470 --> 00:15:16,770
Then don't falter now!

224
00:15:16,770 --> 00:15:18,780
Killing it won't change anything.

225
00:15:18,780 --> 00:15:22,220
Not the blood flowing through your veins, nor the position you find yourself in.

226
00:15:22,220 --> 00:15:24,110
It won't change a single thing!

227
00:15:24,480 --> 00:15:28,400
But you still came here!

228
00:15:28,400 --> 00:15:29,490
So finish the job!

229
00:15:29,490 --> 00:15:31,860
Don't give in to the Hollow Shadow!

230
00:15:32,420 --> 00:15:35,910
Otherwise everything you've done
will have been in vain!

231
00:15:35,910 --> 00:15:36,700
Stab me!

232
00:15:37,260 --> 00:15:38,870
I'm immortal.

233
00:15:41,130 --> 00:15:41,710
So...

234
00:15:42,160 --> 00:15:43,320
So...

235
00:15:45,560 --> 00:15:46,710
live on!

236
00:15:47,560 --> 00:15:48,870
Senpai...

237
00:16:00,510 --> 00:16:02,390
Unleash your blood.

238
00:16:14,030 --> 00:16:14,720
Goodbye.

239
00:16:56,510 --> 00:16:57,390
Senpai...

240
00:16:58,760 --> 00:16:59,370
Hold it.

241
00:17:01,680 --> 00:17:02,410
Stay back.

242
00:17:13,880 --> 00:17:15,090
What's wrong with you?

243
00:17:15,090 --> 00:17:16,970
You went up against the Hollow Shadow, you know?

244
00:17:16,970 --> 00:17:19,030
Didn't you realize this was going to happen?

245
00:17:20,160 --> 00:17:21,600
Forgive me.

246
00:17:22,240 --> 00:17:24,250
I can't guarantee you'll survive this.

247
00:17:24,250 --> 00:17:25,480
I know.

248
00:17:36,960 --> 00:17:39,160
You know that Kanbara-kun's a half-shade, don't you?

249
00:17:39,550 --> 00:17:42,130
When his body falls into a perilous state,

250
00:17:42,130 --> 00:17:44,410
his shade half awakens.

251
00:17:46,570 --> 00:17:48,790
Basically, this is big trouble.

252
00:18:21,370 --> 00:18:23,660
Sen... pai...

253
00:18:29,130 --> 00:18:30,130
The cage!

254
00:18:30,130 --> 00:18:31,920
He can negate our spirit powers.

255
00:18:31,920 --> 00:18:33,010
Ayaka-san!

256
00:18:33,010 --> 00:18:33,710
I know.

257
00:18:44,830 --> 00:18:46,060
Oh no!

258
00:18:57,230 --> 00:18:58,700
No way.

259
00:18:58,700 --> 00:19:00,160
Nino-san!

260
00:19:02,660 --> 00:19:04,930
This'll only hold him for a little while.

261
00:19:06,740 --> 00:19:07,950
Now's our chance!

262
00:19:16,460 --> 00:19:17,360
This isn't working!

263
00:19:17,760 --> 00:19:19,050
He's going to break out!

264
00:19:52,050 --> 00:19:53,710
Do I...

265
00:19:54,410 --> 00:19:56,670
look like a normal person...

266
00:19:57,800 --> 00:19:58,920
to you?

267
00:20:00,670 --> 00:20:02,760
The same goes for me.

268
00:20:05,280 --> 00:20:06,880
I'm sorry.

269
00:20:07,220 --> 00:20:11,240
I didn't understand a thing about you,

270
00:20:12,600 --> 00:20:13,860
and yet I...

271
00:20:15,860 --> 00:20:16,860
I have to stop you.

272
00:21:00,690 --> 00:21:01,650
Kuriyama-san?

273
00:21:14,600 --> 00:21:16,120
I did it again...

274
00:21:17,790 --> 00:21:19,400
She's...

275
00:21:30,910 --> 00:21:32,270
Senpai.

276
00:21:34,560 --> 00:21:35,020
Sorry.

277
00:21:40,980 --> 00:21:42,380
I'm so sorry!

278
00:21:50,070 --> 00:21:51,330
King of Chinese

279
00:21:50,420 --> 00:21:51,330
Thanks for the food!

280
00:21:54,200 --> 00:21:56,140
Slow down and savor it.

281
00:21:56,140 --> 00:21:58,590
I feel like I don't have nearly enough blood!

282
00:21:58,590 --> 00:22:00,480
I need to replenish my iron.

283
00:22:00,480 --> 00:22:02,960
Besides, I can't believe this isn't the Hollow Shadow,

284
00:22:03,960 --> 00:22:07,240
Or that it's only worth 200 yen!

285
00:22:07,240 --> 00:22:09,590
I don't think Ayaka-san would lie, though.

286
00:22:10,000 --> 00:22:11,550
Then what's going on?

287
00:22:13,820 --> 00:22:15,310
How would I know?

288
00:22:20,650 --> 00:22:24,040
Aren't you going to eat?

289
00:22:24,620 --> 00:22:25,150
Nah.

290
00:22:27,660 --> 00:22:29,350
Where are you going?

291
00:22:29,350 --> 00:22:30,290
The restroom.

292
00:22:33,100 --> 00:22:34,210
Hey...

293
00:22:34,210 --> 00:22:34,540
Yes?

294
00:22:35,210 --> 00:22:38,790
Do I look like a normal person to you?

295
00:22:43,150 --> 00:22:44,550
Let's see...

296
00:22:45,520 --> 00:22:48,970
In my eyes, you're nothing but an
ill-mannered guy who's obsessed with glasses.

297
00:22:54,090 --> 00:22:55,100
What the heck?

298
00:23:18,210 --> 00:23:20,580
I've given it some thought since then.

299
00:23:20,580 --> 00:23:22,500
I realized I shouldn't hesitate

300
00:23:22,500 --> 00:23:28,510
\hand that I have to defeat Senpai—
the shade from beyond the horizon.

301
00:23:29,800 --> 00:23:30,800
But I...

302
00:23:31,560 --> 00:23:37,560
I don't want to kill Senpai.

303
00:23:38,330 --> 00:23:41,020
I don't want to... kill him.

304
00:23:44,920 --> 00:23:50,360
I heard that the lull doesn't
actually begin until midnight,

305
00:23:50,360 --> 00:23:56,120
but for some reason, I sense tension in the air.

306
00:23:58,270 --> 00:24:01,460
It's more stagnant than tense, if you ask me.

307
00:24:01,460 --> 00:24:02,590
Lull, eh?

308
00:24:02,590 --> 00:24:03,880
The name fits perfectly.

309
00:24:04,480 --> 00:24:09,380
I should probably walk home
with my little sister right now.

310
00:24:09,380 --> 00:24:12,090
She's long gone, though.

311
00:24:12,090 --> 00:24:13,260
Why?!

312
00:24:13,260 --> 00:24:15,090
Because she doesn't want to
walk home with you.

313
00:24:15,090 --> 00:24:16,230
Why?!

314
00:24:16,230 --> 00:24:17,470
Because she hates you.

315
00:24:17,470 --> 00:24:18,540
Why?!

316
00:24:18,540 --> 00:24:20,180
Because you keep acting like that all the time!

317
00:24:20,690 --> 00:24:25,410
Senpai, I'd better hurry or I won't make it in time for the supermarket's packed meals sale!

318
00:24:25,410 --> 00:24:27,270
Oh, okay.

319
00:24:27,270 --> 00:24:28,020
Later!

320
00:24:29,350 --> 00:24:30,620
Akkey.

321
00:24:31,740 --> 00:24:33,720
Don't take this lightly.

322
00:24:33,720 --> 00:24:34,860
I'm feeling strangely nervous.

323
00:24:37,080 --> 00:24:38,330
Sounds like love.

324
00:24:53,470 --> 00:24:55,090
Want a ride?

325
00:24:55,700 --> 00:24:57,350
I'll give you one.

326
00:25:01,140 --> 00:25:03,100
A lull, huh?

327
00:25:07,530 --> 00:25:08,730
Why are you here?

328
00:25:09,120 --> 00:25:12,860
I figured we could talk a bit while I drive.

329
00:25:17,640 --> 00:25:19,610
Is that a dreamshade?

330
00:25:19,610 --> 00:25:20,770
Yes.

331
00:25:20,770 --> 00:25:27,120
Just like the Hollow Shadow, there are many powerful shades that lack a physical form.

332
00:25:28,190 --> 00:25:34,000
They say this shade was born from all the resentment shown by humans over the years.

333
00:25:34,000 --> 00:25:36,730
It is an entity formed from accumulated malice.

334
00:25:36,730 --> 00:25:43,210
Apparently it'll lead the world to ruin
if left alone, or something.

335
00:25:45,310 --> 00:25:50,650
This dreamshade, said to be the cause of disease, war, and natural disasters,

336
00:25:50,650 --> 00:25:54,190
is also commonly referred to as "the one beyond the horizon."

337
00:25:55,460 --> 00:25:59,410
Thankfully, only a fraction of it has shown up so far—

338
00:25:59,410 --> 00:26:00,660
not enough to be harmful.

339
00:26:01,390 --> 00:26:03,700
Why would you tell me this?

340
00:26:04,210 --> 00:26:09,000
We believe you Nases have the information we need, but you aren't very willing to share.

341
00:26:09,410 --> 00:26:12,720
So I thought I'd try to get it from you.

342
00:26:12,720 --> 00:26:15,990
Looks like they haven't told you anything, though.

343
00:26:16,990 --> 00:26:18,220
Yakiimo.

344
00:26:20,560 --> 00:26:21,800
It's the truth!

345
00:26:22,420 --> 00:26:27,230
So, what is being done about this shade from beyond the horizon?

346
00:26:27,230 --> 00:26:30,650
Do you mean to tell me we Nases have been preparing in secret?

347
00:26:32,730 --> 00:26:34,400
Do you want to know that badly?

348
00:26:39,490 --> 00:26:43,620
Does Kuriyama-san have anything to do with
the shade from beyond the horizon?

349
00:26:44,130 --> 00:26:45,160
Beats me.

350
00:26:45,660 --> 00:26:48,750
But it would be amusing if it did,

351
00:26:48,750 --> 00:26:49,460
don't you agree?

352
00:26:57,140 --> 00:26:58,130
Bro!

353
00:26:58,590 --> 00:26:59,970
Oh dear.

354
00:27:05,820 --> 00:27:09,520
You tailed your little sister all the way here?

355
00:27:09,520 --> 00:27:11,520
It's almost like you have a thing for her.

356
00:27:11,520 --> 00:27:13,260
How you wound me.

357
00:27:13,260 --> 00:27:15,040
The "almost like" part was unnecessary!

358
00:27:21,620 --> 00:27:22,660
What are you after?

359
00:27:22,660 --> 00:27:25,370
Ask your little sister.

360
00:27:33,170 --> 00:27:34,670
Onii-chan!

361
00:27:37,070 --> 00:27:40,260
That was a wonderful display of love for your brother.

362
00:27:48,240 --> 00:27:51,270
Wh-What the heck?

363
00:27:52,900 --> 00:27:56,240
Akihito-kun was run over...

364
00:27:56,240 --> 00:27:57,570
...so why isn't he hurt?

365
00:27:57,570 --> 00:27:58,670
Huh?

366
00:27:58,670 --> 00:27:59,330
Oh, well...

367
00:27:59,330 --> 00:28:01,530
Don't kill us!

368
00:28:01,530 --> 00:28:03,820
Please, don't kill us!

369
00:28:04,910 --> 00:28:07,760
Why would you say that?

370
00:28:28,190 --> 00:28:29,430
Izumi-san?

371
00:28:31,100 --> 00:28:32,600
You must be worn out.

372
00:28:35,020 --> 00:28:37,150
Why are you here?

373
00:28:39,180 --> 00:28:42,530
Get some more rest.

374
00:28:48,740 --> 00:28:51,100
Thank you for riding with us today.

375
00:28:51,100 --> 00:28:53,100
This is Hananodera Station.

376
00:28:53,100 --> 00:28:56,500
Please make sure you have all your belongings.

377
00:28:59,500 --> 00:29:02,510
The obvious conclusion is that the lull's taking its toll on him.

378
00:29:02,930 --> 00:29:08,770
But I have a feeling that it severely weakened
not only his shade half, but also his human half.

379
00:29:08,770 --> 00:29:11,560
Isn't there any way to make him better?

380
00:29:12,370 --> 00:29:15,980
