551
00:40:08,360 --> 00:40:09,790
What are you saying?

552
00:40:09,790 --> 00:40:10,880
What are you saying?!

553
00:40:10,880 --> 00:40:12,770
You should just tell him.

554
00:40:12,770 --> 00:40:13,610
Tell him what?

555
00:40:13,610 --> 00:40:14,960
Tell him what?!

556
00:40:14,960 --> 00:40:15,680
What are you two—

557
00:40:17,300 --> 00:40:18,870
Whoa, it's hot!

558
00:40:19,600 --> 00:40:22,230
It's summer, after all.

559
00:40:25,430 --> 00:40:26,940
Summer, huh?

560
00:40:30,440 --> 00:40:32,500
What? You were here all along—

561
00:40:32,500 --> 00:40:34,460
Whoa, glasses!

562
00:40:36,390 --> 00:40:39,740
How strange. Why am I hearing Akihito's voice?

563
00:40:39,740 --> 00:40:41,160
Am I hallucinating?

564
00:40:41,160 --> 00:40:42,440
Way to go!

565
00:40:42,440 --> 00:40:43,830
Even though sunglasses don't have as much—

566
00:40:45,440 --> 00:40:47,210
Looks like you're the real deal after all.

567
00:40:48,040 --> 00:40:50,450
You'd better leave at once, then.

568
00:40:50,450 --> 00:40:55,970
Letting you ogle my swimsuit-clad body for free is humiliating, to say the least.

569
00:40:55,970 --> 00:40:58,250
Well, I didn't ask you to put it on!

570
00:40:58,250 --> 00:40:59,210
Jeez.

571
00:40:59,210 --> 00:41:00,360
Akihito.

572
00:41:00,360 --> 00:41:00,890
What?

573
00:41:00,890 --> 00:41:05,150
Learn from this and take a long, hard look at yourself.

574
00:41:05,150 --> 00:41:09,770
I never want to go through anything like this again.

575
00:41:13,740 --> 00:41:14,400
Okay.

576
00:41:14,400 --> 00:41:18,200
Also, drag that pervert over there back to the clubroom with you.

577
00:41:18,200 --> 00:41:19,410
Hey, pervert.

578
00:41:20,050 --> 00:41:21,870
What, pervert?

579
00:41:24,350 --> 00:41:27,410
The days are getting shorter and shorter, aren't they?

580
00:41:27,410 --> 00:41:29,880
Well, the summer solstice was back in June.

581
00:41:29,880 --> 00:41:31,370
Want to read some more before we go?

582
00:41:31,370 --> 00:41:32,460
No.

583
00:41:32,460 --> 00:41:35,610
Hiro'omi and Mitsuki sure are taking their time.

584
00:41:35,610 --> 00:41:36,880
They've already left.

585
00:41:36,880 --> 00:41:37,910
What?!

586
00:41:37,910 --> 00:41:42,100
Is that any way to treat someone who
just came back from the brink of death?

587
00:41:42,420 --> 00:41:44,390
Isn't that exactly why?

588
00:41:44,390 --> 00:41:47,470
I'm sure they just don't know how to face you.

589
00:41:49,520 --> 00:41:50,650
What's wrong?

590
00:41:50,650 --> 00:41:52,540
N-Nothing.

591
00:41:55,940 --> 00:41:57,490
Are you free after this, Kuriyama-san?

592
00:41:58,720 --> 00:42:01,830
I thought maybe we could get some dinner on the way back.

593
00:42:01,830 --> 00:42:04,040
Oh, if you're broke, I'll pay.

594
00:42:04,040 --> 00:42:05,410
R-Right...

595
00:42:05,410 --> 00:42:10,250
I mean, I don't remember what happened,
but I'm sure I caused you no end of trouble.

596
00:42:16,360 --> 00:42:19,140
I wish you'd brought it up a little earlier.

597
00:42:19,140 --> 00:42:19,890
Today's no good?

598
00:42:19,890 --> 00:42:21,980
No.

599
00:42:21,980 --> 00:42:25,600
This will probably end once the sun goes down.

600
00:42:25,600 --> 00:42:27,390
What do you mean?

601
00:42:29,430 --> 00:42:30,860
Why...

602
00:42:30,860 --> 00:42:34,860
Why are you so nice to me?

603
00:42:39,700 --> 00:42:42,530
Because we're kinda similar.

604
00:42:43,670 --> 00:42:46,000
If I said that, would you get ma—

605
00:42:46,690 --> 00:42:48,230
Is it that insulting?!

606
00:42:48,230 --> 00:42:50,390
I-It's not like that!

607
00:42:50,390 --> 00:42:53,100
You look like you can't stand
the very thought of it!

608
00:42:53,100 --> 00:42:54,670
D-Does that make you happy?

609
00:42:54,670 --> 00:42:55,800
Why would it?

610
00:42:55,800 --> 00:43:03,200
Well, Mitsuki-senpai told me that you
take extreme pleasure in being bullied,

611
00:43:03,200 --> 00:43:06,220
but I guess it's not that simple.

612
00:43:06,220 --> 00:43:08,100
I'm glad it isn't!

613
00:43:08,100 --> 00:43:10,020
Forget everything Mitsuki told you.

614
00:43:10,020 --> 00:43:11,440
I don't want to!

615
00:43:11,440 --> 00:43:13,350
I won't forget.

616
00:43:14,150 --> 00:43:15,700
I won't ever forget.

617
00:43:20,450 --> 00:43:22,320
What is this?

618
00:43:23,340 --> 00:43:24,800
It's you.

619
00:43:25,330 --> 00:43:27,330
The shade beyond the horizon—

620
00:43:27,330 --> 00:43:32,710
a coalescence of human malice that
\hthey say could lead the world to ruin—

621
00:43:33,550 --> 00:43:37,220
was the dreamshade within you.

622
00:43:37,220 --> 00:43:39,090
That's me?

623
00:43:39,640 --> 00:43:44,720
The whole reason I came to this town was to kill it.

624
00:43:45,770 --> 00:43:48,560
But that didn't go too well.

625
00:43:49,540 --> 00:43:52,640
I simply couldn't bring myself to kill you.

626
00:43:52,640 --> 00:43:54,230
I didn't want to kill you.

627
00:43:55,060 --> 00:43:55,570
So I...

628
00:44:05,700 --> 00:44:09,300
When I heard that I could use my blood

629
00:44:09,300 --> 00:44:13,420
to drive the shade from beyond the horizon
out of you during the lull,

630
00:44:13,420 --> 00:44:16,500
I decided I had to do it at any cost.

631
00:44:28,250 --> 00:44:31,440
What happened to you?

632
00:44:31,440 --> 00:44:32,140
I disappeared.

633
00:44:33,270 --> 00:44:33,690
Then...

634
00:44:34,470 --> 00:44:37,300
Then who is this sitting in front of me?

635
00:44:37,300 --> 00:44:40,190
You haven't regained consciousness yet.

636
00:44:41,190 --> 00:44:45,380
This is all a dream.

637
00:44:45,380 --> 00:44:50,950
The little bit of my blood that's still within you
is what's showing you this dream.

638
00:44:55,340 --> 00:44:57,170
But it's all over now.

639
00:44:57,170 --> 00:45:00,220
You'll wake up soon.

640
00:45:00,220 --> 00:45:00,960
Kuriyama-san...

641
00:45:17,290 --> 00:45:20,500
I thought it'd be easier in a dream,

642
00:45:20,500 --> 00:45:22,650
but it's harder than I expected.

643
00:45:24,410 --> 00:45:25,450
Goodbye.

644
00:45:39,370 --> 00:45:40,620
A dream?

645
00:45:43,630 --> 00:45:45,130
Shindou Photo Studio

